Package set.int64

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    LongSet
    A 64-bit hash set.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    BLPLongHashSet
    An implementation of Amble and Knuth's bidirectional linear probing table, with a simplified insert algorithm from A Concurrent Bidirectional Linear Probing Algorithm, and an original (but trivial) tombstone-free deletion algorithm.
    LCFSLongHashSet
    An implementation of a simple linear probing hash table, with a tombstone-free deletion algorithm taken from _Algorithm Design and Applications_, Section 6.3.3, and the Last-Come-First-Served insertion heuristic.
    LPLongHashSet
    An implementation of a simple linear probing hash table, with a tombstone-free deletion algorithm taken from _Algorithm Design and Applications_, Section 6.3.3.
    RHLongHashSet
    An implementation of a simple linear probing hash table, with the "Robin Hood" insertion heuristic, and a tombstone-free deletion algorithm (note that because we do not use tombstones, we cannot use the maximum insertion probe length to bound the probe length of unsuccessful lookups; instead we use a Robin Hood-specific early termination heuristic).
